--- Numeric types ---

Integer types
- INTEGER(precision)
- DECIMAL(precision, scale)
- MONEY(precision, scale)

Real types
- REAL(precision)
- FLOAT(precision)

precision refers to how many digits are represented,
scale is the magnitude of a number that may be represented.



--- What type is that value? ---
# TYPEOF

some example on SQLSite
> SELECT TYPEOF(1+1);
return integer
> SELECT TYPEOF(1+1.0);
return real
> SELECT TYPEOF('panda');
return text
> SELECT TYPEOF('panda'+'koala');
return integer



--- Ingeter division --- 

> SELECT 1/2
return 0



--- Rounding numbers ---
# ROUND

> SELECT ROUND(2.55555);
return 3
> SELECT ROUND(2.55555, 3);
return 2.556
